narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: This class is truly a masterpiece. Not only is it a very light courseload, it also allows students the opportunity to gain insight into future US naval careers.
You'll learn a bit about the navy and rotc options in the fleet.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Pros: light course-load, Cred/fail grading, you get to wear spiffy naval uniforms, actually-interesting lectures, meets only once/week. Cons: meets on Fridays at 1230-230, and takes up a relatively popular class time slot, preventing midshipmen from taking language classes; worth 0.0 credits
Don't do more than 1 lab per week. Even 1 per week is too many

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I would recommend the class, but emphasize that the lab should be done at a different time, such as earlier in the morning.
obv only if you have to
